{{Quote|The Jedi Order does not intend to remain in control of the executive branch, of course. Conquest was not our aim. Until a new Chief of State can be duly selected, we will be appointing a Triumvirate to act collectively as the Chief of State. It will consist of this one, Senator Treen, and General Jaxton.''"<br />"''Representing the interests of the Jedi, the Senate, and the armed forces, respectively.|Saba Sebatyne, and Wynn Dorvan|<ref name="conviction">''[[Fate of the Jedi: Conviction]]''</ref>}}
The '''Triumvirate''' was the ruling body formed by three prominent figures of the [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances]] to serve as a constitutional replacement for the newly defunct [[Office of the Chief of State]]. After a [[Plan Delta|coup]] carried out by the [[New Jedi Order]] and the [[Lecersen Conspiracy|Lecersen conspirators]] overthrew [[Chief of State (Galactic Alliance)|Chief of State]] [[Natasi Daala]], it was believed by the usurpers that the position of Chief of State was too powerful, as shown by Daala's draconian use of power while in office. In an effort to prevent these abuses from happening again, [[Grand Master/Legends|acting Jedi Grand Master]] [[Saba Sebatyne]] and the leaders of the Lecersen Conspiracy decided to form a Triumvirate. Within the Triumvirate, a majority of votes was required to make decisions and set policies; thus no single individual could hold direct power over the [[Galactic Alliance Defense Force|Armed Forces]] or [[Galactic Alliance Intelligence Service|Intelligence Service]].<ref name="LECG">''[[Legacy Era Campaign Guide]]''</ref> The three members of the Triumvirate were Sebatyne, [[Kuati/Legends|Kuati]] [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] [[Haydnat Treen]], and Galactic Alliance [[Chief of Starfighter Command (Galactic Alliance)|Chief of Starfighter Command]] [[Merratt Jaxton]]. Jaxton was later replaced by [[Wynn Dorvan]].

The Triumvirate ended when, under orders from Grand Master [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]], including the acting Grand Master and Triumvir Saba Sebatyne, withdrew from the Galactic Alliance. This caused the [[Galactic Alliance Senate]] to elect a temporary Chief of State, [[Padnel Ovin]].

Decades later, after the [[Sith–Imperial War]], a Triumvirate was again in operation and submitted to the [[Darth Krayt's Galactic Empire|Empire]] after the defeat and surrender of the Alliance defense force at the [[Battle of Caamas]]. As a condition of the peace, the Imperial regime of [[Roan Fel]] allowed the defeated Triumvirate to remain as [[Viceroy/Legends|viceroys]] governing the remains of [[Galactic Alliance Space|Alliance Space]], though the Triumvirs were replaced by loyal Imperial bureaucrats. Under the overlordship of [[Darth Krayt]], the Triumvirs kept a little of their political power but were still treated as Imperial subjects. By [[137 ABY]], [[Gial Gahan]], one of the former Triumvirs, remained at the [[Mon Calamari Orbital Shipyards]], while secretly providing supplies and weapons to [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Gar Stazi]] and the [[Core Fleet|Galactic Alliance Core Fleet]].

Another government, known as the [[Galactic Federation Triumvirate]], was formed in [[138 ABY]] following the defeat of the Sith Empire. To show unity between the Empire and the wider galaxy, the Triumvirate was led of Galactic Alliance Admiral Gar Stazi, [[Empress/Legends|Empress]] [[Marasiah Fel]] of the Galactic Empire, and [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[K'Kruhk]].

